{"/service/ndnp/sdhi/batch_sdhi_lightning_ver01/data/sn2001063549/00415625017/1908030601/0034.xml":{"full_text":"5}\nii\nffirlS\"**\n\u2022**a\nAfc:\n1\n-f\u00a7y\u00a7\nHE HASTHE PUNCH THAT\nWILL PRODUCE SLEEP.\nThe 'Live Wire\" is Short Circuited and\nBlown Out the Fuse.\nAlderman Charles H. Lester has de\nclared himself a candidate for the chief\nexecutive of the city in. opposition to\nthe present mayor, D. C. Thomas, of\n\"live wire\" fame, who has declared him\nself a candidate for re-election. Both\ncandidates are being strongly backed by\ntheir supporters and friends, and their\nfight will be one to the finish. Alder\nman Lester has declared himself in no\nuncertain terms as to the law enforce\nment and city government, and in this\nho will have the support of the citizens\nwho desire better conditions. M/ Les\nter has served the city long and well as\nan alderman, having served some eight\nyears in that capacity, and has always\nworked for the best interests of its citi\nzens. He has done excellent work on\nthe committee appointed to investigate\nthe water franchise and to a greut ex\ntent is responsible for many of the con\ncessions made by the water company.\nMr. Lester's principal appeal to the citi\nzens is his past record of service.\nPETITION OUT FOB MARTIN\nA petition is being circulated and is\nbeing freely signed by prominent busi\nness men urging John W. Martin to\nenter the mayoralty race, Mr. Martin\nis away at the present time on a trip to\nSeattle, Wash., but is expected back\nsome time this week, and it is not\nknown whether he will accept the nomi\n_*Tintion.' Mr. Miirtin vraathe predecessor\nof the present mayor, and at' tliat time\ndeclined to be- a candidate to succeed\nhimself. In Mr. Martin's case it will be\nthe office seeking the man, and not the\nman the office.\nTHE CITr FATHERS\nIn the fourth ward it looks as if\nAlderman W. B. Kyalls will be chosen\nto succeed himself, and S. B. Sheldon to\nsucceed Alderman Lester. Mr. Ryalls\nhas declared his candidacy, but Mr.\nSheldon has not yet definitely decided'\nto enter the race. Mr. Sheldon has long\nserved the city in the capacity of coun\ncillor, but was defeated two years ago\nby Jas. Forter by a narrow majority.\nMr. Forter subsequently lost his seat by\nremoval to another ward. In the first\nward Alderman F. E. Hawley will be a\ncandidate to succeed himself, while in\nthe second ward Alderman E. Guenther\nwill offer himself for re-election, if a\ndisposition is shown by the people of\nthe ward to have him represent them an\nother term. Alderman Pritchard, his col\nleague in the second ward, has been\nmentioned as a candidate for mayor, but\npositively declines to make the running.\nIn the third ward Alderman Luck will\nno doubt be re-elected if he is willing to\ndeclare himself for re-election.\nTHE BIG TIGHT\nFrom all appearances there does not\na a\ntremendous excitement in the race for\ncouncil honors tho there is every cer\ntainty of a big fight for the mayoralty.\nThe supporters of the different candi\ndates have already taken their stand,\nand the fight will be fought to the bitter\nend. The lines are strongly marked and\neach candidate and every citizen knows\njust what the issue will mean and just\nwhat each candidate will stand for. The\nstruggle has already be\u00a3un|and the sup\nporters of each candidate are being\nlined up for the final struggle at the\npolls.\nFold's Orino Laxative is sold under a\npositive guarantee to cure constipation,\nsick headache, stomach trouble or any\nform of indigestion. If it fails the man\nufacturers refund your money. What\nmore can anyone do.: A. Duffner.\nPoulson's Good Groceries\nHave you paid to much? Are you satisfied to go\non paying the same fancy prices for the groceries\nyou use when we say positively that we can give\nyou the same quality of goods for less money man\nyou have paid before? Don't you owe it to yourself\nto give us a trial?\nOur \"Golden West\" brand of groceries we\nguarantee to be strictly high class. None better on\nthe market and the price is right.\nGolden West Corn, 15c a can, 2 cans 25c\nGolden West Tomatoes, 15c a can, 2 cans 25c\nGolden West Pumpkin, 15c a can, 2 cans 25c v,--H\nGolden West Peas, per can 15c\nGolden West Blackberries, can 20c\nGolden West Grapes, can 20c Golden West Plums, can 25c\nGolden West Pineapples, can 30c\nGolden West Blueberries, per can 20c\nW S a a 2 0\nha Golden West Baked Beans, can 15c\nGolden West String Beans, can 15c\nSPECIALS\n19 pounds Granulated Sugar W. .$1.00\n3 pound package N. BT. C. Crackers 20c\nA. M. Poulson\n-m-\n-w\nThe\nV.\nJ'4*3\nSi.*'\n1\n-itr\\\n1\nI*.\nhiif\niJdsm\nLOCAL NEWS\nGeorge Fuller and Jas. Patterson\nof Henry were ovter here Wtidues\nday.\nM.R. Baakerville\nis\nback\u2022 in the-\ncity shaking hands with his many\nfriends here. -w- 'r\nMrs. Chamberlain is visiting at\nMarshall, Minn., at ttye home of Mr.\nChamberlain's father.\nThe Golden Uagle sells the Gor\ndon hat. Have you seen the new\nspring shfapes? They are fine,\nMrs. S. F. McConnell of Bloom-,\nfield, 111., is in the city viBiting at\nthe home of Mr. and Mrs. Hardy.\nMr. and Mrs. Clyde Huffman and\nMrs. Clark of Bancroft are viaitipg\nat the home of Mr. and Mrs. John.\nGerhart of this city.'\nAdjt Gen. Englesby went to SiB\nseton Wednesday to deliver a spe\ncial invitation to the Elks of that\ntown to come in to the dedication\nfestival next week.\nFor the next thirty days J. W.\nSnyder will take orders for all kinds\nof fruit, shade and ornamental trees\nand shrubbery. Call, him up by\nphone and he will call on you and\ntake your order. Do it today. 37\nThe Fourth Regiment band has\nrented the rooms formerly used as\na gymnasium in the Stacey block,\nand will use them for band practice\nand also as a dance hall.The rooms\nare being fitted up for this purpose\nfor which they are well suited. The\nrooms will be rented to parties\nwishing to give dances, or for any\nother purpose.\nFOE SALE\u2014Here is one of